<DOC><DOCNO> AP900227-0031 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-27-90 0300EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-AlcoholOverdose     02-27 0210</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Alcohol Overdose,0217</SECOND><HEAD>Boy in Coma After Drinking Bourbon</HEAD><DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 5-year-old lapsed into a coma after afriend of his mother's handed him a bottle of bourbon and told himto ``drink it like a man,'' police said.   Anthony Jimerson, 21, of Forest Hills was jailed on $100,000bail on charges of causing injury to a child. Police in suburbanEverman said Raymond Griffin was given the alcohol at a partyFriday night.   ``The guy took the lid off the bottle, gave it to the kid and hetook a big swallow,'' said Sgt. Mark Bigler.   Raymond, who weighs about 60 pounds, drank about 10 ounces ofbourbon _ roughly the equivalent of a fifth of alcohol for anaverage adult, Bigler said.   The boy was in critical condition Monday in a coma at Cook-FortWorth Children's Medical Center, where he was taken Saturday afterhe went into convulsions, authorities said.   At one point, the boy's blood-alcohol level was about .55percent _ more than five times the legal limit for driving in manystates _ and he probably will suffer brain damage, the officer said.   Jimerson had been invited to play dominoes at the home ofRaymond's mother, Patricia Griffin, 31, police said.</TEXT></DOC>